body:
From https://www.reddit.com/r/yosys/comments/fsb0a1/yosys_failed_to_infer_block_ram_when_i_changed/

Minimal example:
```verilog
//module top(input clk, input [3:0] addr, output reg [1:0] dout);
module top(input clk, input [3:0] addr, output reg [0:0] dout);
	reg [1:0] mem[0:15];
	initial begin
		mem[0] = 2'b00;
		mem[1] = 2'b01;
		mem[2] = 2'b10;
		mem[3] = 2'b11;
	end
	always @(posedge clk)
		dout <= mem[addr];
endmodule
```

Run `yosys -p "prep -rdff" memopt.v`

The `dout` register is not merged, and a `$dff` remains. If the first line is uncommented, then the register is merged correctly.

